RIYADH: Honeywell has appointed Abdullah Abdulrahman Al-Juffali as the country president for Saudi Arabia and Bahrain. He will be responsible for driving growth for Honeywell’s operations across four strategic business groups: Aerospace, performance materials and technologies, Honeywell building technologies, and safety and productivity solutions. “Honeywell has been an important partner to Saudi Arabia and Bahrain for more than 70 years. I am proud to lead our businesses to help our customers accelerate the exciting transformation we are witnessing in the Kingdom and beyond,” said Al-Juffali in a press statement. He will also oversee the local design and manufacturing of Honeywell technologies that can drive economic diversification and growth, in line with Saudi Arabia’s National Transformation Plan and Vision 2030, the company said in a press release. “Abdullah brings a proven track record of delivering such initiatives for fast-growth companies in this region, and I am delighted to add his experience in technology and innovation leadership across our business in Saudi Arabia and Bahrain,”  said Mohammed Mohaisen, president and CEO of Honeywell Middle East and North Africa. Honeywell currently operates from nine locations across Saudi Arabia and Bahrain with activities spanning advanced research and development, manufacturing, sales, and administration.